## Implementation Details

The Speed Insights component is correctly implemented according to Vercel's official documentation:

```typescript
// src/app/layout.tsx (lines 3 and 59)
import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        {/* ... other components ... */}
        <SpeedInsights />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This is the recommended approach for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router, placing the component at the end of the body tag in the root layout.

## Next Steps

To activate Speed Insights in production:

1. Deploy the application to Vercel (if not already deployed)
2. Navigate to the Speed Insights section in your Vercel dashboard
3. Select this project and click "Enable"
4. After the next deployment, the tracking routes at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` will be active
5. Monitor performance data in the Vercel dashboard as user traffic accumulates

